Package: ZIFAR
Title: Zero-Inflated Factor Analysis for Single-Cell Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Larry Cai", "", email = "larry.cai@uq.edu.au", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Emma Pierson", "", role = c("aut", "cph")),
    person("Christopher Yau", "", role = c("aut", "cph"))
  )
Description: Native R implementation of Zero-Inflated Factor Analysis (ZIFA) 
    for dimensionality reduction of single-cell data. This algorithm accounts 
    for dropout events (zeros) in single-cell gene expression data. Based on 
    Pierson & Yau (2015) <doi:10.1186/s13059-015-0805-z>.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
